==English==

===Etymology===
From [[Latin]]

===Alternative spellings===
*[[minimise]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb|minimiz|ing}}

# {{transitive}}: To make (something) as [[small]] or as [[insignificant]] as possible.
# {{cattag|computing}} {{transitive}}: To cause a [[window]] to disappear without closing the [[program]] or [[file]] or discarding any [[data]].
#: ''I didn't close anything, but I '''minimized''' all the windows so I could see the [[desktop]].''
